    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>See the <a href=\"http://www.mojohaus.org/exec-maven-plugin/\" rel=\"noreferrer\">exec maven plugin</a>. You can run Java classes using:</p>\n<pre><code>mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass=&quot;com.example.Main&quot; [-Dexec.args=&quot;argument1&quot;] ...\n</code></pre>\n<p>The invocation can be as simple as <code>mvn exec:java</code> if the plugin configuration is in your pom.xml. The plugin site on Mojohaus has a <a href=\"http://www.mojohaus.org/exec-maven-plugin/examples/example-exec-using-plugin-dependencies.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">more detailed example</a>.</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;project&gt;\n    &lt;build&gt;\n        &lt;plugins&gt;\n            &lt;plugin&gt;\n                &lt;groupId&gt;org.codehaus.mojo&lt;/groupId&gt;\n                &lt;artifactId&gt;exec-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n                &lt;version&gt;3.2.0&lt;/version&gt;\n                &lt;configuration&gt;\n                    &lt;mainClass&gt;com.example.Main&lt;/mainClass&gt;\n                    &lt;arguments&gt;\n                        &lt;argument&gt;argument1&lt;/argument&gt;\n                    &lt;/arguments&gt;\n                &lt;/configuration&gt;\n            &lt;/plugin&gt;\n        &lt;/plugins&gt;\n    &lt;/build&gt;\n&lt;/project&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
