    "body" : "<p><code>clean package exec:java -P Class_Containing_Main_Method</code> command is also an option if you have only one Main method(PSVM) in the project, with the following Maven Setup.</p>\n<p>Don't forget to mention the class in the <code>&lt;properties&gt;&lt;/properties&gt;</code> section of <code>pom.xml</code> :</p>\n<pre><code>    &lt;properties&gt;\n        &lt;project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;UTF-8&lt;/project.build.sourceEncoding&gt;\n        &lt;java.main.class&gt;com.test.service.MainTester&lt;/java.main.class&gt;\n    &lt;/properties&gt;\n\n    &lt;plugin&gt;\n      &lt;groupId&gt;org.codehaus.mojo&lt;/groupId&gt;\n      &lt;artifactId&gt;exec-maven-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n      &lt;version&gt;1.2.1&lt;/version&gt;\n      &lt;configuration&gt;\n          &lt;mainClass&gt;${java.main.class}&lt;/mainClass&gt;\n      &lt;/configuration&gt;\n    &lt;/plugin&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p><a href=\"https://spring.io/tools\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">STS</a> Run Configuration along with above Maven Setup:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/OCf1X.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/OCf1X.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\" /></a></p>\n"
