    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>The above mentioned answers are correct but I am simplifying it for noobs like me.Go to your project's pom file. Add a new property <code>exec.mainClass</code> and give its value as the class which contains your main method. For me it was <code>DriverClass</code> in <code>mainpkg</code>. Change it as per your project. \n<a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/LA1GT.png\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/LA1GT.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<p>Having done this navigate to the folder that contains your project's <code>pom.xml</code> and run this on the command prompt <code>mvn exec:java</code>. This should call the main method.</p>\n"
  }, {
